    "Html": "While using --declaration option on the compiler, the emitted output is in ex.:<br />\n<div style=\"color:Black;background-color:White;\"><pre>\r\n<span style=\"color:Green;\">/// &lt;reference path=&quot;Scripts/typings/jquery/jquery.d.ts&quot; /&gt;</span>\n\n<span style=\"color:Blue;\">interface</span> IMyInterface {\n   ....\n}\r\n</pre></div>but I don't want the comment reference because I am not sure about the location of jquery.d.ts on the destination site and I am not sure about the destination of this .d.ts and his relative position with jquery.<br />\n<br />\nAt this time, every time I compile the project I need to remove manually this comment rows.<br />\nI'd like to have a compiler option for this, in ex. --noIncudeReferences or similar<br />\n<br />\nThanks <br />\nGabriele<br />\n",
